itemData.name: EVADER
itemData.description:
The Evader is your new go-to fairway driver. It has controllable speed with excellent glide and enough stability to hold the line, even into the wind. The Evader's 7-speed means that you can count on it to fill the distance gap between your 5-speed midranges and 9-speed fairway drivers, like the Escape or the Getaway. The Evader is extremely versatile, and its consistent fade means that you can work it on anhyzer and know that it will get back to flat. If you're looking for a workhorse fairway driver, the Evader belongs in your bag.

SPEED: 7

GLIDE: 4

TURN: -1.5

itemData.name: PARADOX
itemData.description:
The Paradox is capable of some truly unique lines. High-power players will be using the Paradox for utility shots like rollers, low speed flip ups, massive nose up anhyzers, and other touch shots. Low-power players will find the Paradox is a great first midrange for straight or hyzer-flip flights. Whether you’re using it as a teaching tool, or a utility disc for woods golf, the Paradox’s understability won’t let you down. If you need it to turn, the Paradox is the disc for you!

SPEED: 5

GLIDE: 4

itemData.name: ZONE
itemData.description:

This is a very overstable putter that is good for headwinds, strategic fades, forehand throws, flick putts, and slamming into chains at just the right angle. Many Discraft enthusiasts will have a Zone in their bag as a putter that gets them out of a situation where a Flick, or sidearm putt is their only option. Being so overstable, this disc can handle the torque that a Flick will put on it!

If you are right handed, throw backhand, and need a disc that is going to fly to the right, this is the disc you’re looking for. The Meteor will turn and glide giving beginners more control and distance. The Meteor comes in premium ESP and Z plastics. This is one of the best golf disc plastics on the market, providing superior grip and durability. The Meteor is available in weights between 167-178 grams. Lighter weight discs will turnover more easily.

Choose the Tesla for long-range pinpoint accuracy.

itemData.name: WAVE
itemData.description:
The Wave is a stable-understable high speed distance driver. The Wave is best described as a longer Inertia, with a stable-understable flight profile and a responsiveness that makes it useful across the power spectrum. Available in weights 175g – 155g, the Wave is the type of driver that players may bag in two or more weights for shot variety. For the most powerful throws, long gliding turnovers and hyzerflip gut shots are possible with the Wave. For average powered throws the Wave will simply extend a variety of lines, from anhyzers to hyzerflips to headwind-assisted turnovers.

itemData.name: INSANITY
itemData.description:
THE INSANITY IS A STABLE-UNDERSTABLE DISTANCE DRIVER. The Insanity is best described as a worn-in MVP Inertia, with slightly more high-speed turn and a diminished fade. For average power throwers, the Insanity will be remarkably straight, while high power throwers can execute precise flip and turnover lines with ease. Whether you’re looking for that sweet-spot worn disc flight, or you’re looking to achieve bigger Inertia lines with less power, give Insanity a shot.

itemData.name: FIREBALL
itemData.description:
THE FIREBALL IS AN OVERSTABLE DISTANCE DRIVER. The Fireball is overstable and wind-resistant like the MVP Motion but has an overall straighter and longer flight profile. The Fireball has a longer forward push during its early stage of fade, where the Motion would have begun a long gradual fade. At the end of its flight, the Fireball will drop later and more abruptly than the Motion.

itemData.name: PROXY - GLOW
itemData.description:
THE PROXY IS A STRAIGHT-STABLE PUTT AND APPROACH DISC. The Proxy shares the Envy mold’s core, lending the same low-profile feel and solid grip, along with a short wing width and wide flight plate diameter for superior glide. The Proxy sets itself apart from the Envy with a remarkably straight forward-fading finish. A bit of high-speed turn potential allows the Proxy’s lines to be manipulated over a broad range of power and helps less powerful throwers achieve straight putter drives.

itemData.name: HEX
itemData.description:
Mesmerizingly straight, with flight numbers of 5/5/-1/1, the Hex will find a place in anyone’s bag as a versatile and reliably straight midrange. At the highest arm speeds, the Hex will produce slightly understable lines from flat, but the 1 fade keeps it from flipping over completely. For lower arm speeds, the Hex has enough turn to make shaping lines a breeze. If you are looking for control in the woods, or simply a versatile line shaper, the Hex is the midrange for you.

itemData.description:

Berg is designed for distinct shots, where you don’t need to worry about the disc gliding far passed the basket. The disc features an ergonomic thumb track which is prominent on the top side while not being noticeable at the bottom. This makes it feel very different from any other putter. Berg is Swedish for mountain.

itemData.name: RENTAL - RAD BIRDIE LITE BASKET
itemData.description:
The RAD Birdie Lite disc golf basket is light in weight to make it very portable. Perfect for schools, camps or your backyard, it screws together in seconds with no need for tools.
MDGC has 6 of these baskets that can be rented out across a weekend if the club is not using them for an event.
Pricing: Rental = $50/basket / Weekend + $150 cash deposit/basket to be refunded in full if basket returned with all parts and in same condition
Renter will need to pick-up and return from agreed location around Melbourne as this can change - generally Footscray/Carnegie/Box Hill.
Please call or text Aaron on 0432725987 to discuss timing and pick-up arrangements before renting.
 
Birdie Lite FEATURES
Easy to assemble
Compact and easily transportable
Super lightweight (12kgs)
Strong metal construction - all joints welded
24 high visibility zinc coated chains
Electrophorese anti-rust protection with tough powder coated outer shell
PDGA approved target

itemData.name: TARA ITI
itemData.description:
The RPM Tara iti has a smooth aerodynamic top and a steeper concave under rim. What this means is this disc will soon become one of your favourite control drivers. The smooth top provides good distance and glide and the concave under rim prevents the disc from flipping at high speed. Don't think that because it is a control driver and not a high speed driver that you will lose distance, the testing has shown that the Tara iti can keep up with other speed 12 and 13 discs and gets there with a far more stable flight. Check out our flight testing video. As the disc gets worn in it will make an ideal anhyser disc for holding a left to right line and not burning over (RHBH thrower). Once you throw one it will make your bag.

SPEED: 10

GLIDE: 5

TURN: 0

FADE: 2

"Dynamic Discs is bringing the disc that so many of you have been asking and hoping for. The Felon is here. In the same vein as our game changing Escape, the Felon is a fairway driver that feels great in your hand and comes out easy. Crafted in response to the unforgiving Kansas winds, the Felon is the wind-fighting fairway driver that your bag is calling for. It will continue to sail, without turning over, despite that headwind. When the wind is down, it has an incredibly predictable hyzer finish. When you are facing a low ceiling shot where you need good glide and a strong finish the Felon is your answer."

Speed: 9

Glide: 3

Turn: 0.5

Fade: 4

itemData.name: METHOD
itemData.description:
The Method is an overstable midrange that can handle pro level power on both forehand and backhand shots, and it just got a new best buddy, the Hard Exo version. These discs have a bit lower profile compared to Neo plastic and will make the perfect combination with just about any other mid-range you want to pair it with.

Exo Hard plastic is less durable than Neo, making an excellent disc to cycle through your bag with different levels of stability. Players will notice an overstable flight out of the box and can expect to see more high speed turn over time the more it breaks in.

Pro Tip: Exo Hard plastic is the same composition that we offer in the Link. The durability of these is the same as a putter. Hitting a tree or other obstacles will cause noticeable wear quickly compared to other plastics such as Lux or Neo.

itemData.name: DISCRAFT STARTER SET
itemData.description:
With this set including 1 putter, 1 mid-range, and 1 driver, you will have all the tools you need to start playing disc golf. While there are tons of discs to choose from, the discs in this pack have been specifically picked to cater to players who are new or still learning to play the sport of Disc Golf. These are 3 great discs that will help you get the most out of the sport right from the start.

The Discraft Starter set is all you need to head out for a fun round of disc golf!

These sets contain the following options:

Putter:  Banger GT:  2/3/0/1

Midrange: Buzzz:  5/4/-1/1

Driver: Avenger SS:  10/5/-3/1

Please note: Disc colour and packaging varies and will not necessarily match the disc colours in the image pictured.

itemData.name: HEX - GLOW
itemData.description:
Mesmerizingly straight, with flight numbers of 5/5/-1/1, the Hex will find a place in anyone’s bag as a versatile and reliably straight midrange. At the highest arm speeds, the Hex will produce slightly understable lines from flat, but the 1 fade keeps it from flipping over completely. For lower arm speeds, the Hex has enough turn to make shaping lines a breeze. If you are looking for control in the woods, or simply a versatile line shaper, the Hex is the midrange for you.

itemData.name: PIXEL
itemData.description:
The second disc in the Simon Line is officially here, the Electron Pixel! Debuting with flight numbers of 2 | 4 | 0 | 0.5, the Pixel has a deep profile with a small micro bead, perfect for getting that full grip feeling. Off the tee, the Pixel is a straight/stable flier and will reliably hold any line it’s thrown on with a minimal amount of fade back. However, don’t let the low speed fool you - the Pixel can certainly go the distance, especially with the right wind conditions. On the putting green, whether you’re in C1 or C2, the Pixel shines with the right amount of glide to carry right into the chains.

The release of the Pixel is also the debut of a new blend of Electron Plastic! With an increase in grip and tackiness across the board, and a much softer blend of Soft, the Pixel is truly a culmination of MVP’s and Simon’s years of experience. The putter of choice for 7x Disc Golf Pro Tour winner Simon Lizotte, take your game to the next level with the Electron Pixel!

itemData.name: ZERO GRAVITY - SUPER LIGHT
itemData.description:
Zero Gravity from Latitude 64° – a significant step towards inclusivity in the sport. Developed with young disc golfers and beginners in mind, these are the discs that fly! Full weight discs 170-180 grams are really not suited for beginners and younger disc golfers. But Zero Gravity discs, weighing a mere 120-130 grams thanks to their low-density plastic blend, offer several advantages: ✨ Less Power, More Flight:  🚀 Unmatched Glide:  🌊 They Float!: 
While crafting discs tailored to professional athletes is commendable, it's equally important to cater to those just starting out. By offering discs that are easier to throw and enjoy, we aim to attract more people to this fantastic sport and ensure everyone has a blast playing it!
The current Zero Gravity range includes: PUTTER - PURE: 3/3/0/1 MID-RANGE - FUSE: 5/6/-1/0 FAIRWAY - EXPLORER: 7/5/0/2 FAIRWAY - DIAMOND: 8/6/-3/1 DRIVER - SAINT: 9/7/-1/2

itemData.name: WONDER
itemData.description:
The Wonder by Loop Discs is the straight flying mid we have all been looking for. And we mean straight!  Just when you think it will fade out, the glide holds your line that touch longer than you expect. This disc is the perfect disc for beginners right through to advanced players. We're already calling it the 'one disc wonder' because it's fantastic off the tee, amazing for approach shots, and landing in chains on glidey putts. Everything you need to get started on the course!

Experienced players will love the incredible glide that floats for extra distance on this straight shooting mid.

Best of all, the Wonder, it's 100% Australian made, designed, and owned, using only Australian plastics.

"Flies like a Fuse, but pushes straighter / glides further and can handle torque"  Darren Stace-Smith

SPEED: 5   GLIDE 6   TURN: -1   FADE: 1

Plastic Options:
Soft Touch: This gummy, flexible plastic is slightly lighter, making it ideal for beginners, kids, and players seeking a disc that requires less effort to achieve optimal spin. (~164-170g)
Happy Medium: Balancing grip, flexibility, and durability, this plastic suits players of all skill levels. (~168-174g).

We're already calling it the 'one disc wonder' because it's fantastic off the tee, amazing for approach shots, and landing in chains on glidey putts. Everything you need to get started on the course! Experienced players will love the incredible glide that floats for extra distance on this straight shooting mid. Best of all, the Wonder, it's 100% Australian made, designed, and owned, using only Australian plastics. itemData.name: LATITUDE 64° STARTER SET
itemData.description:
These disc golf sets from Latitude 64° have everything you need to get started with the sport of disc golf!  In this box you will find one driver, one midrange, and one putter. All three have been picked to give beginners to intermediate players the perfect tools to start their disc golfing journey.

The Easy-to-Use Disc Set Includes:

Latitude 64 Retro Burst Diamond (Driver)
Latitude 64 Retro Burst Pearl (Midrange)
Latitude 64 Retro Burst Ruby (Putter)

Discs come in lighter weight range of 155-160 grams, which is perfect for easy handling and control. Colour on stamp is assorted.The Classic Disc Set Includes:

Latitude 64 Retro Burst Saint (Driver)
Latitude 64 Retro Burst Fuse (Midrange)
Latitude 64 Retro Burst Keystone (Putter)  OR Retro Burst Pure (Putter) in the 2.0 Version

Discs come in weight range 170-180 grams. Colour on stamp is assorted.About the Diamond: The Diamond is ideal for beginners, children, and players with lower arm speeds. Its lightweight design makes it easy to throw and control, offering an under-stable flight path with excellent glide and a small fade.
Speed: 8 | Glide: 6 | Turn: -3 | Fade: 1About the Pearl: The Pearl is a user-friendly midrange disc with a small grip and low weight. It has a neutral flight path, making it great for consistent, controlled throws.
Speed: 4 | Glide: 6 | Turn: -4 | Fade: 0About the Ruby: The Ruby is a lightweight putter with a small grip and a straight, neutral flight path. It completes the perfect beginner combo along with the Diamond and Pearl.
Speed: 3 | Glide: 5 | Turn: -3 | Fade: 1About the Saint: The Saint is a highly praised control driver – both among amateurs and pros. When you need a disc with good distance and perfect accuracy the Saint will deliver. Saint will be a straight shooter for long drives and has excellent glide.

Speed: 9 |Glide: 7 | Turn: -1| Fade: 2.
About the Fuse:Fuse is the most versatile midrange driver we have ever made. It has a stable and predictable flight path, and will hold long anhyzer curves with minimal fade at the end.

Speed: 5| Glide: 6| Turn: -1| Fade: 0.
About the Keystone: A good short game is what ties everything together on the course. The Keystone is here to support you. It has a beadless, rounded edge and medium depth. The flight path is under-stable. With the Keystone you will get easy turnovers and straight flights even at low speeds. Build your short game on the Keystone and reach new heights!

Speed: 2| Glide: 5| Turn: -1| Fade: 1.
About the Pure:  The Pure is a modern classic in the putt and approach department. The disc was co-designed with Jesper Lundmark and features a comfortable grip and a medium deep rim, with minimum fade for the ultimate putting experience. Left, straight or right; it will hold any line on your approach shots. Elevate your game around the basket with the Pure.

Speed: 3| Glide: 3| Turn: -1| Fade: 1.
About Retro Line:
The mid-80s was a great time. Disc Golf had just come all the way up to Latitude 64 and we played all through the night in the midnight sun. Translucent discs were far from being invented and all discs were understable with today's standards. We remember those days with nostalgic feelings and wanted a plastic that would remind us of how it used to be. For a long time, we have had requests that we should make discs that could be broken in more easily. Test after test after test led us to this new plastic blend that we have named Retro.

itemData.name: STARTER BAG - DISCMANIA
itemData.description:
The Discmania Starter bag is a great little disc bag for beginners, those who don't carry a lot of discs or those looking to squeeze in a quick round and you don't want to carry your full bag.

Bag features:

Holds 8-10 golf discs
Water resistant with reinforced bottom
Putter pocket
Mesh bottle holder with elastic band
Divided compartments
1 outer zippered pocket to carry keys, wallets, minis, etc.

Colours: Either Black or Black/Grey

Please note: The discs and water bottle in the pictures are not included.

Pro Tip: Get this bag for quick rounds, your starter bag, or for your significant other to get them into disc golf!

itemData.name: TRAIL
itemData.description:

Releasing with flight numbers of 10 | 5 | -1 | 1, throwers of all power levels will find the Trail to be an exceptionally responsive driver for a variety of shot shapes, making the Trail a phenomenal disc for all skill levels.

itemData.name: DETOUR
itemData.description:
Fitting perfectly between the Axiom Hex and MVP Uplink, the newest addition to the James Conrad lineup slides in with flight numbers of 5 | 5 | -2 | 1. As a backhand dominant player, Conrad is known for his beautiful turnover lines, and the Detour excels at those long panning turnovers as well as easy hyzer-flips. Experienced players will find the Detour to be exceptionally easy to manipulate for a wide variety of shot shapes, while newer players will find a delightfully straight flier, perfect for learning the game.

The Latitude 64 River and Latitude 64 Saint are two of the most popular drivers on InfiniteDiscs.com, and have the highest glide ratings of any golf discs currently on the market. The Fury is the newest member of a successful family of high glide discs.

itemData.name: MERMAID
itemData.description:
The Mermaid is never in trouble when water is involved! The Mermaid is Discmania's first floating disc, making it a wise choice when water is nearby. If you throw the Mermaid, you won't have to be afraid of losing your disc in the water!

The Mermaid flies straight through the fairways with a slight turn and reliable fade at the end of its flight. It is a versatile driver for executing a variety of lines. The Mermaid has a mild dome and feels comfortable in the hand. The plastic is extra grippy for use even in wet conditions. It has a medium stiffness with some give on the flight plate.

SPEED: 7

GLIDE: 4

TURN: -1

FADE: 2

itemData.name: DISCMANIA STARTER SETS
itemData.description: This premium but low cost Starter Set from Discmania will get you started on your disc golf journey. Each set consists of a Putter, a stable fairway driver & an under-stable driver to give you the full range of shot shapes in your first set.  The Active plastic is extra grippy for use even in wet conditions. It has a medium stiffness with some give on the flight plate. Putter:   Shogun: 2/4/0/2 OR Sensei: 3/3/0/1 - Straight slow speed for putting and short range approach shots. Mid/Stable Fairway: Maestro: 4/3/0/2 OR Magician: 6/4/0/2 - Mid range drives and approach shots with reliable fade, even in a head wind Under-stable Driver: Genius: 7/5/-4/1 - Long range drives with full S shape for maximum distance. Use downwind or uphill. Can be used as a roller disc Colours vary with each set.

itemData.name: FIREFLY - GLOW VINYL STICKERS
itemData.description:
Are some of your go-to discs not in Eclipse plastic? Fear not, Firefly Glow Vinyl from Hive is here to save your night golf game! These glow vinyl stickers attach easily to any disc and provide a level of glow that, when exposed to UV light, is Eclipse 2.0 on the go. The level of brightness has to be seen to be believed – the brightest glow on the market!

When your round is over, feel free to peel the Firefly Glow Vinyl off and place it back on the sheet for the next round – that’s right, these are easily re-attachable as well! Each sheet has 46 stickers (23 small hexagons and 23 hexagon rings) – plenty of glow for your whole bag. Give every disc the glow it deserves with Firefly Glow Vinyl!

46 stickers per sheet
23 small hexagons
23 hexagon rings
Re-attachable

itemData.name: RANGE
itemData.description:
The Streamline Range is a unique utility disc that fills a specific role in any disc golfer’s bag. Designed for control and precision over distance, the Range lacks glide and drops quickly, making it ideal for those tricky approach shots where overshooting is a risk. With minimal fade and the ability to hold hyzer or anhyzer angles without drifting, it offers a straight, reliable flight that’s surprisingly fun to throw. Comparable to the Kastaplast Berg, the Range brings a similar feel and flight at a more affordable price, making it a must-try for fans of specialized approach discs.
Speed 2

Glide 1

Turn -0.5

Fade 1

itemData.name: ROCKSTAR
itemData.description: Rockstar is a beginner friendly fairway driver from Active Premium Line. Designed with the player in mind, this disc allows easy access to begin opening up your game to untapped distance and control. Golfers with more experience and power will find this disc to be moderately under stable and will display more high-speed turn from the flight. Beginner to intermediate level players are going to enjoy the smooth nature of it’s flight patterns, superb gliding ability, and adaptability to both forehand and backhand throws. Rockstar features a thin rounded nose with gentle wing on the underside of the disc, making for an extremely comfortable fit in your hand. SPEED: 8 GLIDE: 5 TURN: -2 FADE: 1

itemData.name: BALANCE
itemData.description:
The next disc in the Simon Line is primed for its stock release - the Neutron Balance! For those following the development process of this disc, you’ll know there have been three Prototypes released for the Balance, each with minor differences in stability. This allowed Simon to try multiple options and pick the version he prefers most (V2) to go into full production, while giving you all a peek behind the curtain of the process. Settling in with flight numbers of 5 | 5 | 0 | 2, the Balance falls between the MVP Reactor and Axiom Pyro - overstable enough for torque resistance, wind fighting, and a reliable, consistent flight - while still having the flexibility of a midrange for shot shaping. High power players will have a versatile, straight flier with a dependable bite of fade towards the end, while those with less power will find the perfect overstable wind fighting complement to their midrange lineup. The Balance joins the Pixel and Time-Lapse as part of the Simon Line - curated by Simon Lizotte himself. Grab this new addition and experience the Simon Line for yourself!
SPEED: 5GLIDE: 5TURN: 0FADE: 2

itemData.description:
The Uplink is here! MVP’s newest understable midrange, the Uplink is a line shaper’s dream. With a speed of 5, glide of 5, turn of -3, and a fade of 0.5, the Uplink is both a touch straighter and a little easier for power players to control than the Paradox. An extremely versatile disc for players of all arm speeds, this will be the only place to get the Uplink for a while — get yours before they’re all gone!

itemData.name: PEAK
itemData.description:
The Latitude 64 Peak is a low-profile, beaded putter designed for consistency and precision. Inspired by the popular Pure, the Peak offers the same smooth flight with the added control of a small bead. This subtle adjustment enhances grip and provides a touch more stability, making it a dependable choice for putts and precision approach shots. Whether you're inside the circle or attacking the basket from distance, the Peak is built for confident, controlled throws.

itemData.name: PEARL
itemData.description:
The Pearl is another must-have disc created by Latitude 64 for beginners. If you’re looking for the perfect disc for youth, women, and players who have not yet mastered technique, this is it. This light weight disc offers the perfect combination of turn to provide straight accurate throws. Intermediate players will appreciate the Pearl’s ability to go against the grain and slice to the right on backhand throws (for right handed players). The Latitude 64 Pearl can be purchased in the highly durable Opto or Gold Line plastics. This disc will take a beating and maintain its flight characteristics.

itemData.description:
THE INSANITY IS A STABLE-UNDERSTABLE DISTANCE DRIVER. The Insanity is best described as a worn-in MVP Inertia, with slightly more high-speed turn and a diminished fade. For average power throwers, the Insanity will be remarkably straight, while high power throwers can execute precise flip and turnover lines with ease. Whether you’re looking for that sweet-spot worn disc flight, or you’re looking to achieve bigger Inertia lines with less power, give Insanity a shot.

itemData.name: TESLA - GLOW
itemData.description:
The Tesla is a stable-overstable distance driver. The Tesla’s responsive design balances a subtle turn and reliable fade, while a pronounced glide and forward finish gain extra distance. The Tesla extends high power or headwind lines and has plenty of bite to fade back reliably and reduce lateral drift. The Tesla can be considered the big brother to our acclaimed Volt fairway driver. Choose the Tesla for long-range pinpoint accuracy.

itemData.name: WAVE - GLOW
itemData.description:
The Wave is a stable-understable high speed distance driver. The Wave is best described as a longer Inertia, with a stable-understable flight profile and a responsiveness that makes it useful across the power spectrum. Available in weights 175g – 155g, the Wave is the type of driver that players may bag in two or more weights for shot variety. For the most powerful throws, long gliding turnovers and hyzerflip gut shots are possible with the Wave. For average powered throws the Wave will simply extend a variety of lines, from anhyzers to hyzerflips to headwind-assisted turnovers.
SPEED: 11GLIDE: 5TURN: -2FADE: 2

For the most powerful throws, long gliding turnovers and hyzerflip gut shots are possible with the Wave. For average powered throws the Wave will simply extend a variety of lines, from anhyzers to hyzerflips to headwind-assisted turnovers.

TURN: -2

itemData.name: JAWBREAKER SUPER-LITE
itemData.description:
We're proud to officially release our Lightweight Jawbreaker discs as individual options—giving more players access to these unique, ultra-grippy, and easy-to-throw molds.

Originally offered as part of our popular 2023 Black Friday Lightweight Kids Set, these discs quickly became a favorite not only for younger players, but also for anyone working on their form or looking for better performance with slower arm speeds.
Whether you’re a younger player, a beginner building your technique, or a seasoned thrower seeking finesse and control, these Lightweight Jawbreaker discs are a game-changer! 
The current Zero Gravity range includes: PUTTER - CHALLENGER: 3/3/0/1 MID-RANGE - BUZZZ: 5/6/-1/0 DRIVER - SCORCH: 11/5/-2/2

itemData.name: Hot Start (Summer Cup #2) @ Bald Hill - Jan 1, 2026
itemData.description:
The MDGC Summer Cup is a series of 4-6 events across Dec/Jan that are all low cost, no frills & fun events for those that want to play some PDGA tournaments on local Melbourne courses (& 1 a bit further away this year!!).


The Bald Hill Hot Start on Jan 1st is traditionally the first tournament of the New Year globally and will again be run in 2026 on a modified Bald Hill layout.


*** All U18 participants must have a supervision approval form completed and submitted to enable them to play this event. The google form will be linked.. Here. This form must be submitted to the TD atleast 24 hours prior to the event start time to enable groups to be established with parents or approved adults providing supervision.


TD: Zach Schloeffel.   Asst TD: Allen Brunsting

itemData.name: Inaugural Churchill Tournament @ Mathison Park - Jan 11, 2026 (part of Summer Cup)
itemData.description:
Mathison Park, Churchill (Gippsland) is a brand new course that was only opened in Nov 2025. This will be the first ever tournament held there, so hoping that Melbourne players will make the drive East to support this new course and that a few locals might join the fun as well. This will be a 1 day / 2 round PDGA tournament. The start time will be delayed a little to allow for travel and course set-up and the lunch break will include some time for a Come & Try for locals who are new to the game. Please come prepared to assist and grow the sport in this part of Victoria
Players Meeting: 930am
Round 1: 10am-12pm
Lunch and Come & Try: 12-2pm (Note: Club shop will also be open during the lunch break)
Round 2: 2-4pm

itemData.name: 2026 Olinda Classic - March 29th 2026
itemData.description:
For the 3rd year running MDGC will host a pop-up event at the Olinda Precinct (park near community pool). This course has some iconic downhill holes, some touchy postage stamp greens with roll away potential in an amazing place with great mountain views. It is also a test of stamina/fitness!!

For this years event we are moving to March timing to take advantage of longer daylight hours and are looking to add a 10th basket to increase capacity to 50 (still will have 5 person groups).
This is a tough/steep course with some pretty thick rough off the fairway, so please come prepared for a serious walk, wear long pants and there is potential for lost discs.

Note: Birdie Lite baskets are used for about half the holes as the course is steep and they need to be carried in.

*** All U18 participants must have a supervision approval form completed and submitted to enable them to play this event. The google form will be linked.. Here. This form must be submitted to the TD atleast 24 hours prior to the event start time to enable groups to be established with parents or approved adults providing supervision.


TD: Matt Finnigan. Asst TD: Mike Van der Linden

itemData.name: 2026 MDGC Ace Club
itemData.description:
ACE CLUB RULES FOR 2026
The Ace pool has been a part of the MDGC culture for a long time but ever growing number of members and events makes it very difficult to use the traditional ace pool system of collecting cash. Therefore, we have gone to an electronic and easy to manage format.


The rules are simple:
You can buy into the Ace club at any time you like (until the cut off date of Sept 30). Once you do, you will be entered into every remaining social day at each venue for the rest of the season.
The cost of entry will decrease each month. (See the table on the first tab).The Ace pool is spread across all of the social day events for the year so your entry fee will be split into $1 for each remaining rounds for the rest of the year.
We are capping the Ace Pot in 2026. The pot will be capped at $500. When that is reached the accumulated Ace Club funds will start building the next pot.The accumulated pool (up to $500) will be split between all aces for any particular round.
Ace Club memberships can only be purchased from our online store and you are welcome to use your gift cards for the purchase.
We understand that this is not for everyone but will certainly be worthwhile for those who plan to play regularly throughout the 2026 season. It’s a great, set and forget, way to insure your future Aces.
The Ace Club is for Social Days between February and November and does not include Club Champs or other comps, unless they are part of that schedule.
The Ace Club "Early Bird" deal: Is for 2025 Ace club members who renew before Feb 15th - they will receive $5 off the annual entry fee.
I hope this makes sense, but if you have any questions, please contact Allen Brunsting for more information
The Ace Pool tables and who has joined so far can be seen here
